## Q2. Age Group Categorizer

### Given Conditions

* Invalid Age → age < 0 or age > 120
* Child → 0 ≤ age < 13
* Teen → 13 ≤ age < 20
* Adult → 20 ≤ age < 60
* Senior → 60 ≤ age ≤ 120

---

# 1. Boundary Value Test Cases (BVA)

Boundary Value Analysis me hum ranges ke edges check karte hain.
Har boundary ke:

* just below
* at boundary
* just above
  test karte hain.

### Important Boundaries:

0, 13, 20, 60, 120

| Test Case | Input Age | Expected Output |
| --------- | --------- | --------------- |
| 1         | -1        | Invalid Age     |
| 2         | 0         | Child           |
| 3         | 1         | Child           |
| 4         | 12        | Child           |
| 5         | 13        | Teen            |
| 6         | 14        | Teen            |
| 7         | 19        | Teen            |
| 8         | 20        | Adult           |
| 9         | 21        | Adult           |
| 10        | 59        | Adult           |
| 11        | 60        | Senior          |
| 12        | 61        | Senior          |
| 13        | 119       | Senior          |
| 14        | 120       | Senior          |
| 15        | 121       | Invalid Age     |

---

# 2. Equivalence Class Test Cases (ECT)

ECT me har category se ek representative value lete hain.

## Valid Equivalence Classes

* Child: 0–12
* Teen: 13–19
* Adult: 20–59
* Senior: 60–120

## Invalid Equivalence Classes

* age < 0
* age > 120

| Equivalence Class | Sample Input | Expected Output |
| ----------------- | ------------ | --------------- |
| age < 0           | -5           | Invalid Age     |
| 0–12              | 8            | Child           |
| 13–19             | 16           | Teen            |
| 20–59             | 35           | Adult           |
| 60–120            | 75           | Senior          |
| age > 120         | 130          | Invalid Age     |

Difference yaad rakh:

* **BVA** → boundaries ke aas paas values
* **ECT** → har class/range se ek normal value only.
